				 Governor meets injured
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Calcutta, Nov 14: Governor Gopalkrishna Gandhi visited those injured in the Nandigram violence at SSKM Hospital this morning.																								During his 40-minute visit, from 10.20am to 11am, the governor spoke to several patients who suffered bullet injuries in last Saturdays firing on marchers. 																								Gandhi first met Forward Bloc state secretary Ashok Ghosh, admitted to the hospital with respiratory problems. On the way out, he expressed a desire to meet the injured.																								Please ask the chief minister to give us some poison. Only that can end our suffering, Khokon Shith, who feared his father was killed, told Gandhi. 																								Charan Maity, whose daughter Jhuma was injured in the attack, said: My daughter is too traumatised to talk properly. So I told the governor what had happened with her.																								Tapas Khatua said recounting last weeks incidents brought back the horror to his mind. We told him everything.
